<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Voting_system&amp;action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h3>
<div class="references-small references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> One criterion does not necessarily imply the other. For example, range voting complies with participation and consistency, but median ratings satisfies participation and fails consistency.</li>
<li id="cite_note-ambiguous-1">^ <a href="#cite_ref-ambiguous_1-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ambiguous_1-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> The original <a href="/wiki/Strategic_nomination" title="Strategic nomination">independence of clones criterion</a> applied only to ranked voting methods. (T. Nicolaus Tideman, "Independence of clones as a criterion for voting rules", <i>Social Choice and Welfare</i> Vol. 4, No. 3 (1987), pp. 185–206.) There is some disagreement about how to extend it to unranked methods, and this disagreement affects whether <a href="/wiki/Approval_voting" title="Approval voting">approval</a> and <a href="/wiki/Range_voting" title="Range voting">range voting</a> are considered independent of clones.</li>
<li id="cite_note-irviocqualifier-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-irviocqualifier_2-0" title="">^</a></b> Provided a tie-breaker method is used that provides for the elimination of only one of the tied candidates.</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> Results are available in an appendix of his unpublished paper here: <a href="http://math.temple.edu/~wds/homepage/rangevote.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://math.temple.edu/~wds/homepage/rangevote.pdf" rel="nofollow">[1]</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-mactutorhistory-4">^ <a href="#cite_ref-mactutorhistory_4-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-mactutorhistory_4-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-mactutorhistory_4-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFJ._J._O.27Connor_and_E._F._Robertson">J. J. O'Connor and E. F. Robertson. <a href="http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/HistTopics/Voting.html" class="external text" title="http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/HistTopics/Voting.html" rel="nofollow">"The history of voting"</a>. <i>The MacTutor History of Mathematics Archive</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/HistTopics/Voting.html" class="external free" title="http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/HistTopics/Voting.html" rel="nofollow">http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/HistTopics/Voting.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on October 12 2005</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+history+of+voting&amp;rft.atitle=The+MacTutor+History+of+Mathematics+Archive&amp;rft.aulast=J.+J.+O%27Connor+and+E.+F.+Robertson&amp;rft.au=J.+J.+O%27Connor+and+E.+F.+Robertson&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk%2F%7Ehistory%2FHistTopics%2FVoting.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Voting_system"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-dogeelection-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-dogeelection_5-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMiranda_Mowbray_and_Dieter_Gollmann">Miranda Mowbray and Dieter Gollmann. <a href="http://www.hpl.hp.com/techreports/2007/HPL-2007-28R1.html" class="external text" title="http://www.hpl.hp.com/techreports/2007/HPL-2007-28R1.html" rel="nofollow">"Electing the Doge of Venice: Analysis of a 13th Century Protocol"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.hpl.hp.com/techreports/2007/HPL-2007-28R1.html" class="external free" title="http://www.hpl.hp.com/techreports/2007/HPL-2007-28R1.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.hpl.hp.com/techreports/2007/HPL-2007-28R1.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on July 12 2007</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Electing+the+Doge+of+Venice%3A+Analysis+of+a+13th+Century+Protocol&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Miranda+Mowbray+and+Dieter+Gollmann&amp;rft.au=Miranda+Mowbray+and+Dieter+Gollmann&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hpl.hp.com%2Ftechreports%2F2007%2FHPL-2007-28R1.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Voting_system"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFJ._J._O.27Connor_and_E._F._Robertson">J. J. O'Connor and E. F. Robertson. <a href="http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/Mathematicians/Condorcet.html" class="external text" title="http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/Mathematicians/Condorcet.html" rel="nofollow">"Marie Jean Antoine Nicolas de Caritat Condorcet"</a>. <i>The MacTutor History of Mathematics Archive</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/Mathematicians/Condorcet.html" class="external free" title="http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/Mathematicians/Condorcet.html" rel="nofollow">http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/Mathematicians/Condorcet.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on October 12 2005</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Marie+Jean+Antoine+Nicolas+de+Caritat+Condorcet&amp;rft.atitle=The+MacTutor+History+of+Mathematics+Archive&amp;rft.aulast=J.+J.+O%27Connor+and+E.+F.+Robertson&amp;rft.au=J.+J.+O%27Connor+and+E.+F.+Robertson&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk%2F%7Ehistory%2FMathematicians%2FCondorcet.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Voting_system"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFG._H.C3.A4gele_and_F._Pukelsheim2001">G. Hägele and F. Pukelsheim (2001). "<a href="http://www.math.uni-augsburg.de/stochastik/pukelsheim/2001a.html" class="external text" title="http://www.math.uni-augsburg.de/stochastik/pukelsheim/2001a.html" rel="nofollow">Llull's writings on electoral systems</a>". <i>Studia Lulliana</i> <b>3</b>: 3–38<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.math.uni-augsburg.de/stochastik/pukelsheim/2001a.html" class="external free" title="http://www.math.uni-augsburg.de/stochastik/pukelsheim/2001a.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.math.uni-augsburg.de/stochastik/pukelsheim/2001a.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Llull%27s+writings+on+electoral+systems&amp;rft.jtitle=Studia+Lulliana&amp;rft.aulast=G.+H%C3%A4gele+and+F.+Pukelsheim&amp;rft.au=G.+H%C3%A4gele+and+F.+Pukelsheim&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.pages=3%E2%80%9338&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.math.uni-augsburg.de%2Fstochastik%2Fpukelsheim%2F2001a.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Voting_system"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
